{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Now I have all I need. Three issues found:", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:48:36+00:00", "time": "22:48:36"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "1. **`parse_qwscan` silently fails** if the module outputs `+QWSCAN:55,...` without a space — it checks for `\"+QWSCAN: \"` (9 chars with space) but the outer filter only checks `\"+QWSCAN:\"` (8 chars). Format mismatch → every line silently skipped.", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:48:36+00:00", "time": "22:48:36"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "2. **No raw-line trace** → no visibility into what the module actually returns.", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:48:36+00:00", "time": "22:48:36"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "3. **`fc41d_getline` in the scan loop** uses a single 18 s timer that starts at entry and is **not refreshed** across blank lines — if the module sends many blank lines before the first `+QWSCAN:` line, the timer can expire.", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:48:36+00:00", "time": "22:48:36"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Fixing all three now:", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:48:36+00:00", "time": "22:48:36"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:48:41+00:00", "time": "22:48:41"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "  ▶ Edit  C:\\CCoreAI\\DirectClaude\\DirectClaude\\projects\\13-wifi-scan\\Core\\Src\\fc41d.c", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:48:41+00:00", "time": "22:48:41"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Now fix `FC41D_WifiScan` to echo every raw line and reset the per-line timer correctly:", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:48:43+00:00", "time": "22:48:43"}
