{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "ST-LINK probe is found but reports `Voltage: 0.00V` — the target board is **not powered**. Power the board on and run the flash command again.", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "Once the board is powered I'll flash it. You can re-run:", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "```", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "STM32_Programmer_CLI.exe -c port=SWD freq=4000 -w projects\\13-wifi-scan\\build\\Debug\\wifi_scan.elf -rst", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "```", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "---", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**Summary of what was fixed** (build is ready to flash):", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "| # | Fix | Why |", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "|---|---|---|", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "| 1 | `parse_qwscan`: space after colon is now optional | Module may output `+QWSCAN:55,...` without space; the old check `\"+QWSCAN: \"` (9 chars) silently rejected every line |", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "| 2 | `FC41D_WifiScan`: every raw line from the module is now echoed as `[UART9] <line>` | No visibility before; now you can see exactly what the module sends |", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "| 3 | Added `parse_qwscan failed` message when a `+QWSCAN:` line passes the prefix filter but fails to parse | Catches remaining format edge cases |", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**Expected trace after fix:**", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "```", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "[FC41D] AT+QWSCAN (WiFi scan, up to 18 s)...", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "[UART9] AT+QWSCAN              ← echo from module (if echo not fully disabled)", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "[UART9] +QWSCAN:55,3,MyNet,AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "[FC41D] AP  1:   -45 dBm  WPA2  AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF  MyNet", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "[UART9] OK", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "[FC41D] WifiScan done: 1 network(s) found", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "```", "ts": "2026-05-16T19:49:27+00:00", "time": "22:49:27"}
